				<td colspan="2"><span>Daehron is exactly right.  The other thing that is funny about the fight is that the mez works as a memblur on you.  The other scarelings leave you alone for those 20 sec.  So you just have to be not suprised by the imp when he apoears.  If you are prepared he isn't *that* tough.  A lot of Wizards and SKs really shorten the time of the fight down.  If you know ahead of time that your entire raid is going to be out of it for 20 seconds every 30, then you can plan ahead.
<br />

<br />
I can not overstate the size of this AoE.  The mez effect has a HUGE radius (the 200 above is actually off a bit, its *500*), it will reach from the wall (old break in point) all the way to the zone in.</span></td>
