			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: The change in Po fear really blows.<a name="27735"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 15 04 10:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>We've crossed paths with the Ireblind Imp a couple of times.  Pertinent info:
<br />

<br />
1.  The Imp himself isn't really the problem.  The problem is chain agro adds.  Ascher has this one close -- mez isn't really a memblur, but when they changed the code a year or so back so that pets wouldn't break mez, it meant that no NPCs will ever break mez.
<br />

<br />
For a little while, there was a sploit whereby we could mez ourselves and NPCs would stop attacking.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, it's not quite a memblur though -- the mobs don't forget about you they just lose interest in attacking you while your mezzed.  You stay on the hate list, and they pass the hate list to any of their buddies they happen to pass.  So, imagine the scenario:
<br />

<br />
- Agro Ireblind and 2 friends.  Ireblind AE mezzes everyone, 2 friends leave, now bored.
<br />
- They tell 2 friends about those jerks by the zone.
<br />
- Mez wears off.  Ireblind and 4 friends come back.  Ireblind AE mezzes.
<br />
- 4 friends tell 4 more friends.
<br />
- etc.  Eventually someone strolls past Fright, Dread, or Terror.  Then you hear &quot;Fright shouts &quot;Irena!&quot;&quot; when mez breaks.
<br />

<br />
How kick a$ is that?
<br />

<br />

<br />
2.  Best tactic I have heard of so far relies on Necros, SKs, and Shammies.  Necros &amp; SKs use lich, which is enough dot damage to break mez.  Shammies all cast Pox of Bertox on themselves. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
3.  Our enchanters report that Ireblind cannot be mezzed and cannot be stunned.
<br />

<br />

<br />
4.  My experiments suggest he does not immediately fire that mez.  The day after some ugly wipeage, I zoned in with DA up and an insta click gate potion just to see what I could figure out.  Ireblind agro'd me at the IZ and I was able to kite him all the way down to the south wall.  He never mezzed me.  Maybe he won't mez unless either (a) he takes some damage or (b) he sees more than one target.  I do not know which.
<br />

<br />

<br />
5.  He spawns out of a random scareling and that becomes his permanent bind point, to which he will path whenever he loses agro.  Relevance to you and your ministry:  If you're doing a west wall break, you d*mn well better not kill any scarelings.  If you do, you'll have an Ireblind Imp bound right by the zone in.  Better to hold scarelings mezzed, then move to north or south walls and kill them there.  
<br />

<br />
That way, if you do spawn the Ireblind, he's parked a safe distance away from the zone, and rebreaks aren't quite so difficult.
<br />

<br />

<br />
6.  Ireblind has, for Fear, a really small agro radius.  If you can park him on north or south walls, it would be quite possible to clear the rest of the zone without fighting him.
<br />

<br />
Further bulletins as events warrant. . . . . .</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
